Package com.illposed.osc

Provides the Java OSC API, which should be everything users of this library need.
  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    AddressSelector
    Checks whether an OSC Address Pattern fulfills certain criteria.
    OSCListener
    Allows to listen to incoming messages that match some selector pattern.
    OSCPacket
    OSCPacket is the abstract superclass for the various kinds of OSC Messages.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    OSCBundle
    A bundle represents a collection of OSC packets (either messages or other bundles) and has a time-tag which can be used by a scheduler to execute a bundle in the future, instead of immediately.
    OSCImpulse
    An OSC 1.0 optional, and OSC 1.1 required argument type.
    OSCMessage
    An simple (non-bundle) OSC message.
    OSCPort
    OSCPort is an abstract superclass, to send OSC messages, use OSCPortOut.
    OSCPortIn
    OSCPortIn is the class that listens for OSC messages.
    OSCPortOut
    OSCPortOut is the class that sends OSC messages to a specific address and port.
